name: Eternal Gloop
release_bio: The 38th release from WHY? Record Company (WRC) - WHY038
The 1st WRC release of the year from whythough?

The "Eternal Gloop EP" by whythough? (Ian Rios) is a four track driving trance techno journey consisting of bangers to play at 3AM. You'll hear these songs played right after the scheduled time for the venue to close, while all the people who listen to generic techno leave, the gurners get a chance to make their way to the front to stay for "One More Song!" or 20 minutes while the DJ mixes these four tracks into one long final encore.
Recorded, Produced, Mixed, and Mastered by whythough?
Artwork by Ian Rios
A WRC Blue Label Release
